write a JavaScript program to generate and print out the ascii character and hexadecimal codes for 0 to 7f
Here's a simple JavaScript function that generates ASCII characters and their corresponding hexadecimal values from 0 to F (15 decimal):
```javascript
function charToHex(char) {
    const hexChars = '0123456789ABCDEF';
    let i = 0;

    while (i < 16 && char.toLowerCase() >= 'a' && char.toLowerCase() <= 'f') {
        if (char === String.fromCharCode(hexChars.charCodeAt(i) + 97)) { // Add 97 to match ASCII values
            return hexChars.substring(0, 2);
        } else {
            i++;
        }
    }

    throw new Error(`Unsupported character: ${char}`);
}

function asciiToHex() {
    for (let i = 0; i <= 7F; ++i) {
        const char = String.fromCharCode(i);
        console.log(charToHex(char));
    }
}

asciiToHex();
```
This code defines two functions: `charToHex` and `asciiToHex`. The former function takes a character as input, converts it to lowercase for case-insensitive comparison, and returns its corresponding hexadecimal value. The latter function iterates through all ASCII characters from 0 to F (15 decimal) using a for loop, calls the `charToHex` function for each character, and prints the resulting hexadecimal values in the console.
